            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-14T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-14T12:00:00-05:00" n="280" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.516 Export-Import Bank/5–1448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Brazil</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-14T13:00:00-04:00">May 14, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>371. For Conf <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>. Board Directors <gloss target="#t_Eximbank1">Eximbank</gloss> May 12 approved application Baldwin
                    Locomotive Co for commitment to finance sale 130 locomotives for Departamento
                    Nacional de Estrada de Ferro. Value order about $14 million of which <gloss target="#t_Eximbank1">Eximbank</gloss> will agree finance $8,330,000.
                    Obligor to be National Dept Railways and obligations to be guaranteed by Banco
                    do Brasil. Credit to be amortized over 5 year period starting six months from
                    date delivery with interest 4 percent. Application approved with provisions that
                    this commitment also available any other US bidders for same business; that it
                    be automatically cancelled at end three months if not accepted by a US
                    manufacturer subject however to another three months extension upon request
                    interested bidder; and that financing be available until Dec 31 1949. It must be
                    clearly understood that is merely commitment to Baldwin to permit them present
                    offer of sale to Railways. No order has yet been placed and Brazil authorities
                    not aware this proposal. Bank strongly recommends and Dept concurs that this
                        <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss> not be repeated outside <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
